# Clean Code Architecture

- Use TypeScript throughout and prefer explicit, composable types for public interfaces.
- Keep components modular, focused, and reusable; split large UI into feature-oriented sections.
- Separate concerns across `components`, `lib`, and feature modules.
- Prefer small pure utilities, typed props, and predictable data flow.
- Keep naming clear and consistent, and avoid dead code or overly complex abstractions.
